<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-531-570  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 531 570.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  June 11 1990 v7 n23 p28(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Auto-Run 2.0 gains decision-making, password features. (AutoSoftInc. to ship new version of Auto-Run automation utility) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sullivan, Kristina B.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   AutoSoft Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Auto-Run 2.0 (Utility program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Utility ProgramsSecurity SoftwareProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Kristina B. SullivanandM;AutoSoft Inc. plans to ship this week a new version of its Auto-Run PCautomation utility that adds decision-making capabilities and passwordprotection.andM;Like the earlier release, Auto-Run 2.0 is designed to automate repetitivetasks and run applications on unattended PCs.andP;  For example, Auto-Run 2.0 canbe used to generate reports or to perform unattended communications sessions,according to Phil Petree, president of AutoSoft in Smyrna, Ga.andM;The new release has been enhanced with decision-making features, allowingusers to initiate computing tasks via &quot;if .andP;  .  .  then&quot; statements.andM;This capability lets users direct Auto-Run to search for a particular word orstring of text and, if found, to activate a specific task.andM;Auto-Run 2.0's other new features include full menuing capabilities, on-linehelp, password protection, support for holiday scheduling and the ability toinsert text from an ASCII file, Petree said.andM;Auto-Run 2.0 is priced at $149.95; current users can upgrade for $35.andM;AutoSoft Inc. can be reached at (800) 252-7144.andO;</TEXT></DOC>